It’s a language to talk to relational databases.
Stores data in tables, like spreadsheets.
Tables have columns (fields) and rows (records).

Read data → SELECT
Insert data → INSERT
Update data → UPDATE
Delete data → DELETE
Define schema → CREATE TABLE, ALTER TABLE

-----------------------------------------
SELECT user_login, user_email FROM wp_users WHERE ID = 2;
INSERT INTO wp_users (user_login, user_email) VALUES ('bob', 'bob@mail.com');
UPDATE wp_users SET user_email='alice_new@mail.com' WHERE ID = 2;
DELETE FROM wp_users WHERE ID = 1;

CREATE TABLE posts (
    ID INT NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
    post_title VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    post_author INT NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (ID),
    FOREIGN KEY (post_author) REFERENCES users(ID)
        ON DELETE CASCADE
        ON UPDATE CASCADE
);